  "text": "The static floor field S does not evolve with time and is not changed by the presence of pedestrians. Such a field can be used to specify regions of space which are more attractive, e.g. an emergency exit (see the example in [CITATION_1] ) or shop windows. This has an effect similar to a position-dependent matrix of preference, but is much easier to realize.",
